Faith isn't always a comfort.

255
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,395
I've lost so many over the years.

256
00:21:56,320 --> 00:22:01,952
God blesses every child, born and unborn,
with an immortal soul.

257
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,070
All I can do is pray for them,

258
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:09,550
especially the unbaptized ones,
wherever they may go.

259
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:14,310
Aren't they all allowed into heaven?

260
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,871
I just assumed.

261
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:25,479
But we can hope
that God, in His infinite mercy,

262
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:30,714
will one day still welcome them
into His eternal communion.

263
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:35,436
And may He do the same for me.

264
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,552
What have you got for me?

265
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,835
Lamb chops.
I thought you might be hungry.

266
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:16,193
Oh, Lucy, please
don't tell me you've come empty-handed.

267
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:19,674
What is it?

268
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,192
A few grains of opium.

269
00:24:29,320 --> 00:24:31,117
How did you know where to get this?

270
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:36,230
Don't be angry,
but I followed you one night.

271
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,837
You got it from Ping Wu?

272
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:44,280
I'm sure he took quite a liking to you.

273
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:47,994
As long as you didn't have
to put your golden lotus

274
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:50,036
in his mouth to pay for it.

275
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:53,637
Could you grab that lamp and matches?

276
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:02,353
And light the lamp for me.

277
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:26,119
Just hold that over the flame.

278
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,752
Am I doing it right?

279
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,994
Just, uh, just hold it over here.

280
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:26,356
How did you pay for this?

281
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:30,319
My bicycle.

282
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:20,919
-Good morning, Dr. Edwards.
-Good morning.

283
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,592
Nurse.

284
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:25,433
I'm afraid it's just
the two of us on the ward today.

285
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:29,229
Oh. Well, doesn't appear to be anything
the pair of us can't handle.

286
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,228
Shall we?

287
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:36,913
Mr. Oates.

288
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:42,278
I want you to open your eyes for me.
And, please, don't be alarmed.

289
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:43,475
I'm a colored man.

290
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:47,269
Don't make any difference to me.

291
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:56,874
Doctor?

292
00:27:56,960 --> 00:28:00,077
Patient presents
capsulocretaceous cataracts in both eyes.

293
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,388
I advise surgery.

294
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:02,799
Anesthetic?

295
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:05,235
In the absence of cocaine,
I'd recommend Holocaine.

296
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,512
Looks like we are meeting halfway.

297
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,670
It would seem so.

298
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:20,799
My father says
that's a sure sign of any good relationship.

299
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:24,072
I was just headed to see if
Dr. Thackery needed anything.

300
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,752
Hmm.

301
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:29,150
You've been awfully solicitous
of Dr. Thackery lately.

302
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:31,071
Should I be jealous?

303
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:35,396
What do you mean?

304
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:38,358
-No, I just...
-What did you think?

305
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:41,238
Nothing. Um...

306
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,629
Mr. Barrow is looking for you.

307
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:47,159
No, Sir, I did not say that.

308
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,958
And I do sympathize with your situation.

309
00:28:49,080 --> 00:28:51,878
I just wish you'd show
a bit of sympathy for mine.

310
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,910
No, sir, I have not had that privilege.

311
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,194
Good bye.

312
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:00,668
Horse-trading?

313
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:03,638
The army's requisitioned the lot
from the German Hospital.

314
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:07,072
Waiting to arrange shipment
to the US military post at Havana Harbor.

315
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:10,914
They can't be persuaded to part
with a lousy hundred bindles or so?

316
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,753
- The army would never miss 'em.
- Not for love or money.

317
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:18,391
Well, that's the Germans for you.

318
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:21,756
Never been a race better
at squeezing the life out of a dime.

319
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,671
I thought that was the Jews.

320
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:28,198
Nice of you to grace us
with your presence this morning.

321
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,112
How's Dr. Thackery? Better?

322
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:35,556
No better.
The drugs you gave me were salt water.

323
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:40,553
-Can you get your money back?
-I don't think so.

324
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,312
Do you happen to speak any German?

325
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:43,879
-What?
-Nothing.

326
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:45,951
Go to work, Lucy.

327
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:48,634
It's going to be a very long day.

328
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:56,033
Dr. Thackery.
Always a pleasure.

329
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,074
What can I do for you today?

330
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:01,675
It's more a question of what
I can do for you.

331
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:06,678
I have agreed to accept your offer

332
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:10,996
to endorse Thackery's Rejuvenating Liniment.

333
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:13,549
Uh-huh.

334
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:20,078
I think you mean
Peter's Rejuvenating Liniment.

335
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:27,792
He's a fine doctor.

336
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:29,833
Natural-born salesman, too.

337
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,399
Can't you peddle two of them?

338
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:34,276
That ship has sailed, Doc.

339
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:37,033
In fact, it might be
the only ship that's sailed around here lately.

340
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:41,514
That damn war in the Philippines
has interrupted my supply of narcotics.

341
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:44,160
They're prohibitively expensive
if they can be found at all.

342
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:48,677
I venture to guess that's the reason
for your coming here today?

343
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:50,796
What's in this stuff anyway?

344
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:54,190
Oh, blackstrap and
whatever else I can find for an added kick.

345
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:56,794
-Cocaine?
-Would if I could find any.

346
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,308
Mr. Luff,

347
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:12,509
would you consider
giving me a small advance

348
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:16,189
in earnest of the day
when the war is over

349
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:19,397
and you can sell one of these
with my name on it?

350
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,872
I'm afraid I can't help you.

351
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:27,598
Well, then I'm afraid

352
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:31,556
I will be forced to go to your competition.

353
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:35,391
I'm afraid they won't help you either.

354
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:42,076
You see, in our line of work,
a man has to present to the customer

355
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:45,152
a convincing air of healthful vitality.

356
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:51,233
Not to mention trustworthiness
and incorruptibility.

357
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:54,869
Please, please, please, please.
I'll do anything.

358
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:58,157
Yes, that is exactly my point.

359
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:01,519
Now, if you'll unhand me, sir,

360
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:04,831
this moldy rogue
has some business to attend to.

361
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:33,114
Nurse. Nurse. Nurse!

362
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,878
I don't think I know you.

363
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:37,954
No, ma'am.

364
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,270
They sent me over
from the hospital's nursing school.

365
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:41,918
Surgical specialty.

366
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:44,673
Well, you should have come
to see me straightaway.

367
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:48,316
I'm Nurse Braun,
Superintendent of Nurses.

368
00:32:48,840 --> 00:32:50,637
Nurse...

369
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,312
Thackery.

370
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:54,118
Welcome, Nurse Thackery.

371
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:58,916
Scrub in and report to Herr Dr. Schmidt
in the main surgery.

372
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,672
Where is that, ma'am?

373
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:03,672
The other end of this corridor on the left.

374
00:33:03,760 --> 00:33:07,435
And where is the drug dispensary, ma'am,
in the event I'm asked to fetch something?

375
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:09,636
Across the hall from it.

376
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,073
Thank you, ma'am.

377
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:07,432
What do you think you are doing?

378
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:10,193
Dr. Schmidt asked me
to fetch him some supplies, ma'am.

379
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:12,635
-Excuse me, ma'am.
-What's under your cape? Show me.

380
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:14,950
I said remove your cape. Stop her!

381
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:16,789
Stop that woman!

382
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:55,078
Get undressed in there.

383
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:10,950
Do you want me to get completely undressed?

384
00:35:11,040 --> 00:35:12,792
Yes, it's advisable.

385
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:22,789
Because I'll be bleeding?

386
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:29,032
The procedure is called
dilation and curettage.

387
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:32,036
The cervix is dilated

388
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:37,194
and an instrument called a curette
is inserted to remove the...

389
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,228
Tissue.

390
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:44,036
Will it hurt?

391
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:46,594
No, you'll be etherized.

392
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:51,959
Cover yourself with this.

393
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,279
Algie.

394
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,512
Algie.

395
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:26,997
Algie, why won't you look at me?

396
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:44,236
I can perform the procedure,
but I cannot perform it on you.

397
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:47,478
You have to.

398
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:50,234
Please.

399
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:55,075
I can't kill my own child.

400
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:59,030
What are the alternatives?

401
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:08,272
We could sail to Europe.

402
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:13,439
Liberia.

403
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:17,712
They're more tolerant there.

404
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,552
Europe? Liberia?

405
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:22,200
There's no place on earth
we can raise it, Algie.

406
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,998
-Shh.
-Are you insane?

407
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,677
We have no choice.

408
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,558
I'm sorry.

409
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:51,269
-I can't.
-Algie.

410
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:55,798
-Please.
-I can't.

411
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:30,228
Well done, Nurse Elkins.

412
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:48,712
Here, let me do it.

413
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:02,636
You're a resourceful girl.

414
00:40:05,560 --> 00:40:07,152
You're the most

415
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,631
resourceful,

416
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:15,151
most wonderful,

417
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:18,319
beautiful girl

418
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:23,150
I have ever known.

419
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:35,996
Oh, you.

420
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,637
Wait, let's douse your sex with it.

421
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:04,108
No.

422
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:06,478
Let's douse yours.

